Interface Root

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Owned, Parent, PlaceEntity
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Root

    public interface Root
extends Parent, PlaceEntity
    Roots describe regions of the bigraph. These are the roots of the place graph structure and compose its outer interface. Roots (like sites) are identified within a bigraph by their index (position).
